2.1.3 Regression model

x=as.factor(data1$Covid)
table(x)
## x
## After state of alarm                     NO      State of alarm 1 
##                    92                   319                    77 
##      State of alarm 2 
##                   148
y=as.numeric(data1$euros)
x=relevel(x, ref = "NO")
z=data1$kgs

Model<-glm((y)~x,family=Gamma(link=log))
cooksd <- cooks.distance(Model)
influential <- cooksd[(cooksd > (3 * mean(cooksd, na.rm = TRUE)))]
influential=as.numeric(names(influential))
y=y[-influential]
xaux=x[-influential]
Model<-glm((y)~xaux,family=Gamma(link=log))
summary(Model)
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = (y) ~ xaux, family = Gamma(link = log))

##                    88                   225                    49 
##      State of alarm 2 
##                   131
y=as.numeric(data1$euros)

z=data1$kgs


Model<-glm((y)~x,family=Gamma(link=log))
cooksd <- cooks.distance(Model)
influential <- cooksd[(cooksd > (3 * mean(cooksd, na.rm = TRUE)))]
